        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:22PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Lancaster, or 5 miles north of Fort Lawn, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Lawn, Richburg, Catawba, and Edgemoor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
